@subsection GCC for Windows

Written and maintained by Seth Galbraith (@email{sgalbrai@@krl.org}).

Andrew Zabolotny, myself and others are working on instructions for using
Crystal Space with a GNU compiler for windows, but it isn't easy because of
the many different versions of the GNU Windows compiler and problems with
some Windows header files containing non-standard code used by Microsoft.
If you're interested in helping out with this project, contact me or one of
the other Crystal Space developers.

